Nollywood Actress, Mary Remmy-Njoku, expressed her gratitude to God as she clocked a new age on Sunday. On her Instagram page, Njoku announced her birthday, as she called her new age a “year of bliss”. She noted that some people didn’t make it to her age and some would never do, hence her gratitude. Sharing a picture of herself, the founder of ROK TV channels promised to live life to the fullest. She wrote, “Happy Birthday #mamaObi. I am blessed. And I know it. So many people didn’t make it to this age and some wouldn’t. But I am here. “God, I am grateful for another year of bliss. And I promise to live it to the fullest, so help me God. Happy Birthday.” Husband of the actress, Jason, also took to his Instagram story to celebrate his wife. Sharing a picture of them at a vacation, Jason wrote, “Happiest birthdays @maryremmynjoku.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com